Tammy Petersen, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - Seven men accused of abducting and gang-raping a 13-year-old girl will spend the week behind bars.The youths, aged between 18 and 20, appeared in the Wynberg Magistrate's Court on Friday.The matter was postponed to November 25 for the bail application. Police are searching for another suspect in connection with the attack which took place on Friday night in Nyanga. The girl had been walking alone on Robert Sobukwe Road at about 20:00 when she was abducted by a man who took her to a shack where he and his friends repeatedly raped her.&nbsp;She was held overnight and released the next day.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.